Cascading = automatic action on child table when parent table is
updated or deleted

It is used in FOREIGN KEY constraints

CREATE TABLE orders (
    order_id INT,
    customer_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (customer_id)
    REFERENCES customers(id)
    ON DELETE CASCADE
);

Types of Cascading :

✅ ON DELETE CASCADE

👉 When parent row is deleted → child rows also deleted automatically

✅ ON UPDATE CASCADE

👉 When parent key is updated → child table updates automatically